---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'AI Website Builder Cost Breakdown: Is It Worth It? (2025)',
  description: 'AI website builders cost $0-30/month. Here\'s the real cost breakdown including hidden fees, when it\'s worth it, and when you\'re overpaying.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['AI website builder cost', 'AI website builder pricing', 'website builder price comparison', 'cheap AI website'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Pricing Breakdown Â· Hidden Costs Revealed
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        AI Website Builder Cost: Is It Worth It?
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        AI website builders cost $0-30/month on the surface. But there are hidden costs. Here's what you're actually paying.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: Free tiers are powerful but limited. Paid tiers ($15-25/month) unlock real features. Premium tiers ($50+/month) are for businesses with specific needs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Price Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      AI Website Builder Prices: Side-by-Side
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Tool</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Free Tier</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Pro Tier</th>
            <th class="p-4 border font-bold">Premium Tier</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border font-bold"><strong>Durable.co</strong></td>
            <td class="p-4 border">3 sites, basic features</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$12/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$20/mo</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="p-4 border font-bold"><strong>v0.dev</strong></td>
            <td class="p-4 border">100 generations/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$20/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$40/mo</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="p-4 border font-bold"><strong>Framer</strong></td>
            <td class="p-4 border">2 sites, Framer branding</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$15/mo</td>
            <td class="p-4 border">$25+/mo</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Hidden Costs -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      The Hidden Costs Nobody Mentions
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hidden Cost #1: Custom Domain</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Most free tiers don't include custom domains. You're stuck with yoursite.builder.com.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Real cost: $10-15/year for domain name, or upgrade to paid tier ($15-25/mo)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hidden Cost #2: Builder Branding</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Free tiers often show "Built with X" badges or footers. Looks unprofessional for business.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Real cost: Upgrade to paid tier ($15-25/mo) to remove branding</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hidden Cost #3: Limited AI Generations</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Free tiers cap AI generations. v0.dev allows 100/mo (generous). Others may limit more strictly.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Real cost: Upgrade or wait for monthly reset</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hidden Cost #4: Analytics & SEO Tools</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Advanced analytics, SEO optimization, and integrations often require paid tiers.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Real cost: Upgrade ($15-25/mo) or use third-party tools (extra cost)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hidden Cost #5: Storage & Bandwidth</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Free tiers limit storage and bandwidth. Hit the limit and your site slows or shuts down.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Real cost: Upgrade for more resources, or optimize images/content</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">Hidden Cost #6: Export Fees</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">Some builders charge extra to export your code. Others don't allow export at all.</p>
        <p class="font-bold">Real cost: Choose v0.dev if export matters, or rebuild from scratch later</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When Free is Enough -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When Free Tier is Actually Enough
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">âœ… Personal portfolio</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Free tier works fine. Builder branding doesn't matter much for personal sites. You can always upgrade later.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">âœ… Testing & prototyping</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Use free tiers to test different builders. See what you like before paying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">âœ… Temporary landing page</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Running a short-term campaign? Free tier is perfect. No need to pay for something temporary.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">âœ… Side projects & experiments</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Testing ideas? Use free tier. Upgrade only if it gains traction.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- When to Pay -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      When Paid Tier is Worth It
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">ðŸ’¼ Business website</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Custom domain and no builder branding are non-negotiable. Pay the $15-25/month. It's worth it for credibility.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">ðŸ“ˆ Need analytics</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">If you need to track visitors, conversions, SEO â€” paid tier includes these tools. Third-party analytics add cost and complexity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">ðŸš€ High traffic</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Free tiers have bandwidth limits. If you're getting real traffic, upgrade or your site will slow down.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">ðŸŽ¨ Advanced features</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Custom code, advanced integrations, API access â€” these require paid tiers. If you need them, you need to pay.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-black mb-3">ðŸ’° Client work</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Building sites for clients? Paid tier is mandatory. Builder branding on client sites is unprofessional.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROI Calculator -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      ROI: When Does It Pay for Itself?
    </h2>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="text-lg font-bold mb-4">The math is simple:</p>
      
      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
        <p><strong>Scenario 1: You hire a web designer</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Cost: $500-5,000+ for a basic site</li>
          <li>Time: 2-6 weeks</li>
          <li>AI builder cost: $15-25/month</li>
          <li><strong>ROI: Pays for itself in 1-3 months vs hiring</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Scenario 2: You build it yourself (no AI)</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4">
          <li>Cost: Your time (20-100 hours)</li>
          <li>Learning curve: Steep</li>
          <li>AI builder cost: $15-25/month</li>
          <li><strong>ROI: Pays for itself in saved time</strong></li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Scenario 3: Business revenue impact</strong></p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
          <li>Professional site = credibility</li>
          <li>Credibility = more customers</li>
          <li>If it brings ONE extra customer: ROI is immediate</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-2 border-purple-600 rounded-xl p-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black mb-4">Bottom Line</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">Free tier = fine for testing. Paid tier ($15-25/mo) = worth it for anything serious. Premium tier ($50+/mo) = only if you need specific advanced features.</p>
      <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">The real cost isn't the subscription. It's rebuilding your site 3 months later because you chose the wrong tool.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      Related Guides
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/how-to-choose-ai-website-builder" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">How to Choose the Right Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Decision framework</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/best-ai-website-builder-small-business" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Best for Small Business</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Small business use cases</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
